<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<MissionPlan xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="missionplan.xsd">
    <CompositeTaskInformation>
        <!-- From the starting point, find a tree somewhere in the middle of the orchard and measure cos. If low reading, go to and take 2 pictures of nearby trees. From there, measure another tree as far away as possible for co2 and repeat the same process. Once done, take a temperature reading at any one of the northernmost trees. Finally, return to end. -->
        <TaskDescription>Original question</TaskDescription>
        <SubTasks>
            <!-- Drive to the middle tree -->
            <DriveToLocation>
                <Start>
                    <GeoJSON>
                        <Point>
                            <coordinates>-122.4194,37.7749</coordinates>
                        </Point>
                    </GeoJSON>
                </Start>
                <End>
                    <!-- Middle tree coordinates -->
                    <GeoJSON>
                        <Point>
                            <coordinates>[Middle tree longitude], [Middle tree latitude]</coordinates>
                        </Point>
                    </GeoJSON>
                </End>
            </DriveToLocation>
            <!-- Measure cos at the middle tree -->
            <MeasureCos>
                <TreeType>[Middle tree type]</TreeType>
            </MeasureCos>
            <!-- If low reading, go to and take 2 pictures of nearby trees -->
            <If condition="cos_reading_low">
                <Then>
                    <!-- Drive to a nearby tree -->
                    <DriveToLocation>
                        <Start>
                            <!-- Middle tree coordinates -->
                            <GeoJSON>
                                <Point>
                                    <coordinates>[Middle tree longitude], [Middle tree latitude]</coordinates>
                                </Point>
                            </GeoJSON>
                        </Start>
                        <End>
                            <!-- Nearby tree coordinates -->
                            <GeoJSON>
                                <Point>
                                    <coordinates>[Nearby tree longitude], [Nearby tree latitude]</coordinates>
                                </Point>
                            </GeoJSON>
                        </End>
                    </DriveToLocation>
                    <!-- Take pictures of the nearby tree -->
                    <TakePictures>
                        <TreeType>[Nearby tree type]</TreeType>
                    </TakePictures>
                </Then>
            </If>
            <!-- Drive to another tree as far away as possible for co2 measurement -->
            <DriveToLocation>
                <Start>
                    <!-- Nearby tree coordinates -->
                    <GeoJSON>
                        <Point>
                            <coordinates>[Nearby tree longitude], [Nearby tree latitude]</coordinates>
                        </Point>
                    </GeoJSON>
                </Start>
                <End>
                    <!-- Far tree coordinates -->
                    <GeoJSON>
                        <Point>
                            <coordinates>[Far tree longitude], [Far tree latitude]</coordinates>
                        </Point>
                    </GeoJSON>
                </End>
            </DriveToLocation>
            <!-- Measure co2 at the far tree -->
            <MeasureCo2>
                <TreeType>[Far tree type]</TreeType>
            </MeasureCo2>
            <!-- If low reading, go to and take 2 pictures of nearby trees -->
            <If condition="co2_reading_low">
                <Then>
                    <!-- Drive to a nearby tree -->
                    <DriveToLocation>
                        <Start>
                            <!-- Far tree coordinates -->
                            <GeoJSON>
                                <Point>
                                    <coordinates>[Far tree longitude], [Far tree latitude]</coordinates>
                                </Point>
                            </GeoJSON>
                        </Start>
                        <End>
                            <!-- Nearby tree coordinates -->
                            <GeoJSON>
                                <Point>
                                    <coordinates>[Nearby tree longitude], [Nearby tree latitude]</coordinates>
                                </Point>
                            </GeoJSON>
                        </End>
                    </DriveToLocation>
                    <!-- Take pictures of the nearby tree -->
                    <TakePictures>
                        <TreeType>[Nearby tree type]</TreeType>
                    </TakePictures>
                </Then>
            </If>
            <!-- Drive to a northernmost tree -->
            <DriveToLocation>
                <Start>
                    <!-- Far tree coordinates -->
                    <GeoJSON>
                        <Point>
                            <coordinates>[Far tree longitude], [Far tree latitude]</coordinates>
                        </Point>
                    </GeoJSON>
                </Start>
                <End>
                    <!-- Northernmost tree coordinates -->
                    <GeoJSON>
                        <Point>
                            <coordinates>[Northernmost tree longitude], [Northernmost tree latitude]</coordinates>
                        </Point>
                    </GeoJSON>
                </End>
            </DriveToLocation>
            <!-- Take pictures of the northernmost tree -->
            <TakePictures>
                <TreeType>[Northernmost tree type]</TreeType>
            </TakePictures>
        </If>
        </If>
    </If>
</If>

In this mission, the robot will navigate to multiple locations based on sensor readings and take pictures of specific trees. The mission is structured using If-Then statements to handle different scenarios based on the sensor readings.

The robot will start at a known location (not specified in the mission) and navigate to the first tree for measuring cos. If the reading is low, it will go to a nearby tree and take pictures. After that, it will move to another tree for co2 measurement. If the co2 reading is also low, it will go to a nearby tree and take pictures again. Finally, it will navigate to a northernmost tree and take pictures before returning to its starting location.

The mission uses nested If-Then statements to handle multiple conditions and actions based on sensor readings. The robot's actions are clearly defined, making the mission easy to understand and implement.